f10IfExtensionMib.name: f10IfExtensionMib

revisions.description: Initial version of this mib module.

f10IfExtensionMib.description: Dell Networking OS IF Extenstion MIB.

f10IfTable.name: f10IfTable
f10IfTable.description: Dell Networking OS Extension ifTable contains generic interface parameters.

f10IfEntry.name: f10IfEntry
f10IfEntry.description: A row defintion of Dell Networking OS Interface Extension parameters.

f10IfIpMtu.name: f10IfIpMtu
f10IfIpMtu.description: The IP (Internet Protocol), Maximum Transmission Unit value.

f10IfDuplexMode.name: f10IfDuplexMode
f10IfDuplexMode.description: Duplex mode of the interface. This will be read-write only for s60

f10IfRxFlowCtrl.name: f10IfRxFlowCtrl
f10IfRxFlowCtrl.description: Flow control receive. This will be read-write only for s60

f10IfTxFlowCtrl.name: f10IfTxFlowCtrl
f10IfTxFlowCtrl.description: Flow Control transmit.This will be read-only only for s60

f10IfDescr.name: f10IfDescr
f10IfDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This will be read-write only for s60

f10IfAdminStatus.name: f10IfAdminStatus
f10IfAdminStatus.description: A admin status of any interface. This will be read-write only for s60

f10IfRateInterval.name: f10IfRateInterval
f10IfRateInterval.description: The rate info interval for the interface. This will be read-write only for s60

f10IfSpeed.name: f10IfSpeed
f10IfSpeed.description: The interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. This will be read-write only for s60

f10IfPortListBitPos.name: f10IfPortListBitPos
f10IfPortListBitPos.description: This is used for identifying the bit position in PortList Object for a given interface.

f10IfStaticsTable.name: f10IfStaticsTable
f10IfStaticsTable.description: The statistcs information of the interfaces for performance monitoring.

f10IfStaticsEntry.name: f10IfStaticsEntry
f10IfStaticsEntry.description: A row defintion of Dell Networking OS Extension interface statistics.

f10IfInVlanPkts.name: f10IfInVlanPkts
f10IfInVlanPkts.description: The total number of valid VLAN Tagged frames received.

f10IfIn64BytePkts.name: f10IfIn64BytePkts
f10IfIn64BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but in-cluding FCS octets).

f10ifIn65To127BytePkts.name: f10ifIn65To127BytePkts
f10ifIn65To127BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (ex-cluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

f10IfIn128To255BytePkts.name: f10IfIn128To255BytePkts
f10IfIn128To255BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

f10IfIn256To511BytePkts.name: f10IfIn256To511BytePkts
f10IfIn256To511BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

f10IfIn512To1023BytePkts.name: f10IfIn512To1023BytePkts
f10IfIn512To1023BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

f10IfInOver1023BytePkts.name: f10IfInOver1023BytePkts
f10IfInOver1023BytePkts.description: The total number of frames received that were longer than 1023 (1025 Bytes in case of VLAN Tag) octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed. This counter is not incremented for too long frames.

f10IfInThrottles.name: f10IfInThrottles
f10IfInThrottles.description: This counter is incremented when a valid frame with a length or type field value equal to 0x8808 (Control Frame) is re-ceived.

f10IfInRunts.name: f10IfInRunts
f10IfInRunts.description: The total number of frames received that were less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

f10IfInGiants.name: f10IfInGiants
f10IfInGiants.description: The total number of frames received that were longer than 1518 (1522 Bytes in case of VLAN Tag) octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed. This counter is not incremented for too long frames.

f10IfInCRC.name: f10IfInCRC
f10IfInCRC.description: The total number of frames received that had a length (ex-cluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but had a bad CRC.

f10IfInOverruns.name: f10IfInOverruns
f10IfInOverruns.description: The total number of frames dropped because of buffer issue.

f10IfOutVlanPkts.name: f10IfOutVlanPkts
f10IfOutVlanPkts.description: The Number of Good VLAN Tagged Frames sent successfully.

f10IfOutUnderruns.name: f10IfOutUnderruns
f10IfOutUnderruns.description: The total number of frames dropped because of buffer underrun.

f10IfOutUnicasts.name: f10IfOutUnicasts
f10IfOutUnicasts.description: The Number of Good Unicast Frames sent successfully.

f10IfOutCollisions.name: f10IfOutCollisions
f10IfOutCollisions.description: A count of the frames that due to excessive or late collisions are not transmitted successfully.

f10IfOutWredDrops.name: f10IfOutWredDrops
f10IfOutWredDrops.description: A count of the frames that are dropped using WRED policy because of to excessive traffic.

f10IfOut64BytePkts.name: f10IfOut64BytePkts
f10IfOut64BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was 64 Bytes.

f10IfOut65To127BytePkts.name: f10IfOut65To127BytePkts
f10IfOut65To127BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was in the range of 65 to 127 Bytes.

f10IfOut128To255BytePkts.name: f10IfOut128To255BytePkts
f10IfOut128To255BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was in the range of 128 to 255 Bytes.

f10IfOut256To511BytePkts.name: f10IfOut256To511BytePkts
f10IfOut256To511BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was in the range of 256 to 511 Bytes.

f10IfOut512To1023BytePkts.name: f10IfOut512To1023BytePkts
f10IfOut512To1023BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was in the range of 512 to 1023 Bytes.

f10IfOutOver1023BytePkts.name: f10IfOutOver1023BytePkts
f10IfOutOver1023BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was greater than 1023 Bytes.

f10IfOutThrottles.name: f10IfOutThrottles
f10IfOutThrottles.description: This counter is incremented when a valid frame with a length or type field value equal to 0x8808 (Control Frame) is sent.

f10IfLastDiscontinuityTime.name: f10IfLastDiscontinuityTime
f10IfLastDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which this interface's counters suffered a discontinuity via a reset. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

f10IfInCentRate.name: f10IfInCentRate
f10IfInCentRate.description: This is the ingress rate in percentage. This is an integer value which can go from 0 to 100.

f10IfOutCentRate.name: f10IfOutCentRate
f10IfOutCentRate.description: This is the egress rate in percentage. This is an integer value which can go from 0 to 100.

f10IfExtensionMibCompliance.name: f10IfExtensionMibCompliance
f10IfExtensionMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for Dell Networking OS IF Extension MIB.

f10IfParamsGroup.name: f10IfParamsGroup
f10IfParamsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the Dell Networking OS IF Extenstion parameters.

f10IfStatsGroup.name: f10IfStatsGroup
f10IfStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the interface statistics.
